Banco Bilbao, Alba, Ezentis, Mota-Engila: Iberia Stock Preview

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-09-01T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/banco-bilbao-alba-ezentis-mota-engila-iberia-stock-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading today.
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  rose 3.2 percent to 8,718.60.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  climbed 2.4 percent to 6,320.08.  Spanish stocks:  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  : Morgan
Stanley initiated coverage of Spain’s second-biggest bank with
an “overweight” recommendation. The shares climbed 4 percent
to 6.34 euros.  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  : Morgan Stanley initiated
coverage of Spain’s biggest bank with an “equal-weight”
recommendation. The shares climbed 4.4 percent to 6.42 euros.  Corporacion Financiera Alba SA (ALB SM): The investment
holding company said in a filing to regulators that first-half
net income climbed 91 percent from a year earlier to 284 million
euros ($409 million). The shares rose 1.8 percent to 34.30
euros.  Grupo Ezentis SA (EZE)  : The telecommunications and
construction company said it refinanced 20 million euros of
loans to support its photovoltaic business. The shares jumped
4.4 percent to 19 euro cents.  Portuguese shares:  Mota-Engil SGPS SA (EGL)  : Portugal’s biggest
construction company said net income in the second-quarter
dropped 24 percent to 12.6 million euros. The company also said
it won contracts in  Peru . Shares dropped 2.4 percent to 1.33
euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Charles Penty in Madrid at 
 cpenty@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
